                    <p>
                        Dr. Wu has been the Director-General of the Taiwan Food and Drug Administration (TFDA) since February 2017. Under her leadership, TFDA has made best efforts in overcoming great challenges to ensure the safety, efficacy, and quality of food, medicinal products, medical devices, and cosmetics.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Dr. Wu actively promotes international cooperation, including the advancement of regulatory harmonization, establishment of cooperative arrangements, and sharing of regulatory experiences with different countries. She recently led TFDA to become a full member of the International Cooperation on Cosmetics Regulation (ICCR) and an APEC Training Center of Excellence (CoE) for Regulatory Science in medical devices.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Before joining TFDA, Dr. Wu was the Dean of the College of Pharmacy at Kaohsiung Medical University, where she received her Ph.D. degree. She also served as a visiting fellow of University of Tokushima and University of Virginia in 2001. Her areas of expertise include: pharmacy, instrumental analysis, nanotechnology, bioanalytical technology (drugs, genes, and proteins), toxicology, and cosmetics.
                    </p>
